# Prompt Template: Documentation (API/Component Docs)

**Version**: v1.0  
**Purpose**: Generate comprehensive API and component documentation from code  
**Output Format**: Markdown (Swagger/OpenAPI format when applicable)  
**Complexity**: Low-Medium

---

## Template Parameters

Replace placeholders with your values:

- `{PROJECT_CONTEXT}` — E.g., "Election Voting API (.NET Core 10)"
- `{TARGET_TYPE}` — E.g., "API Endpoint", "Service Class", "Angular Component"
- `{NAME}` — E.g., "Elections Controller" or "EmployeeService"
- `{FILE_PATH}` — E.g., "backend/ElectionVoting.Api/Controllers/ElectionsController.cs"
- `{LANGUAGE}` — E.g., "C#", "TypeScript"
- `{AUDIENCE}` — E.g., "Backend Developers", "Frontend Developers", "API Consumers"
- `{STYLE}` — E.g., "Technical", "Comprehensive", "Quick Reference"
- `{INCLUDE_EXAMPLES}` — true/false

---

## Prompt Template

```
Documentation Request
====================

Project: {PROJECT_CONTEXT}
Target Type: {TARGET_TYPE}
Name: {NAME}
File: {FILE_PATH}
Language: {LANGUAGE}
Audience: {AUDIENCE}
Documentation Style: {STYLE}
Include Code Examples: {INCLUDE_EXAMPLES}

Documentation Structure
======================

Generate documentation with these sections:

**Overview** (1-2 sentences)
- What does this do?
- Why does it exist?
- Key responsibility

**Purpose & Use Cases**
- Primary purpose
- When to use this
- When NOT to use
- Related components/endpoints

**Key Features / Methods** (if applicable)
- List main methods/endpoints
- Brief description of each
- Parameters/inputs
- Return types/outputs

**Detailed Method Documentation** (if applicable)
For each method/endpoint:

- **Method Name**: Exact signature
- **Description**: What it does (2-3 sentences)
- **Parameters**: 
  - Name: {param_name}
  - Type: {type}
  - Required: Yes/No
  - Description: {description}
  - Example Value: {example}
- **Returns**: 
  - Type: {return_type}
  - Description: {description}
  - Example Value: {example}
- **Throws/Errors** (if applicable):
  - Error Type
  - When it occurs
  - Solution/How to handle
- **Example Usage**:
  - Code snippet showing usage
  - Expected output

**Dependencies & Integration**
- Other components this depends on
- External services called
- Database tables accessed
- Configuration needed

**Security Considerations**
- Authentication required: Yes/No
- Authorization requirements
- Sensitive data handling
- Security best practices

**Performance Notes**
- Performance characteristics
- Optimization tips
- Known bottlenecks
- Scaling considerations

**Testing Guide**
- How to test this component
- Key test scenarios
- Mock setup if needed
- Expected test results

**Troubleshooting** (if applicable)
- Common issues and solutions
- Debug tips
- Error messages and meanings

**Related Documentation**
- Links to related docs
- Cross-references
- Standard patterns used

**Examples** (if {INCLUDE_EXAMPLES} = true)
- Complete working examples
- Real-world scenarios
- Before/After patterns
- Common variations

Format Requirements
===================

- Use Markdown for formatting
- Code blocks with language syntax highlighting
- Tables for parameter lists
- Bullet lists for features
- Clear section headers (##)
- Subsections with ###
- Example code blocks with ```language
- No more than 80 characters per line
- Professional, clear tone

Audience Considerations
======================

For {AUDIENCE}, emphasize:
- Backend Developers: Architecture, dependencies, patterns
- Frontend Developers: APIs, data contracts, error handling
- API Consumers: Endpoints, status codes, request/response formats
- DevOps: Deployment, configuration, monitoring
- Product Managers: Purpose, features, use cases

Status Indicators
=================

Include status for:
- [ ] Version (e.g., v1.0, v1.1)
- [ ] Last Updated: Date
- [ ] Status: (Stable, Beta, Deprecated)
- [ ] Maintainer: (if known)
- [ ] Breaking Changes: (if upgrade)

Quality Checklist
=================

Documentation is complete when:
- [ ] Overview clearly explains purpose
- [ ] All public methods documented
- [ ] Parameters fully described
- [ ] Return values explained
- [ ] Examples provided (if requested)
- [ ] Error cases documented
- [ ] Security considerations noted
- [ ] Integration points explained
- [ ] Related docs linked
- [ ] Professional, consistent tone
```

