## Example: API Endpoint Documentation (C#)

```
Documentation Request
====================

Project: Election Voting API (.NET Core 10)
Target Type: API Endpoint
Name: Get Election Results
File: backend/ElectionVoting.Api/Controllers/ElectionsController.cs
Language: C#
Audience: API Consumers (Frontend/Mobile Developers)
Documentation Style: Comprehensive
Include Code Examples: true

---

## GET /api/elections/{electionId}/results

**Overview**
Retrieves voting results for an election, including vote counts per candidate.
Only the organization that owns the election can access results.
Results are returned in real-time once election is closed.

**Purpose & Use Cases**
- Display election results dashboard in UI
- Generate reports on voting outcomes
- Export results data for analysis
- Monitor ongoing elections

**Parameters**

| Name | Type | Required | Description |
|------|------|----------|-------------|
| electionId | int | Yes | The ID of the election to retrieve results for |
| organizationId | int | (inferred) | From authenticated user context |

**Response**

**Success Response (200 OK)**
```json
{
  "electionId": 123,
  "electionName": "Manager Selection 2026",
  "totalVotes": 145,
  "candidates": [
    {
      "candidateId": 1,
      "name": "John Smith",
      "voteCount": 89,
      "percentage": 61.4
    },
    {
      "candidateId": 2,
      "name": "Jane Doe",
      "voteCount": 56,
      "percentage": 38.6
    }
  ],
  "statusCode": 200,
  "timestamp": "2026-04-08T14:30:00Z"
}
```

**Error Responses**

| Status | Scenario | Message |
|--------|----------|---------|
| 400 | Invalid election ID | "Election ID must be a positive number" |
| 401 | Not authenticated | "Authentication required. Use Authorization header" |
| 403 | Wrong organization | "You do not have access to this election" |
| 404 | Election not found | "Election not found" |
| 422 | Election still open | "Election results only available after closing" |

**Example Request**

```bash
curl -X GET https://api.example.com/api/elections/123/results \
  -H "Authorization: Bearer {token}" \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json"
```

**Example Response**

```json
{
  "electionId": 123,
  "electionName": "Manager Selection 2026",
  "status": "Finalized",
  "totalVotes": 145,
  "candidates": [
    {
      "candidateId": 1,
      "name": "John Smith",
      "voteCount": 89,
      "percentage": 61.4
    }
  ]
}
```

**Security**
- Requires Valid JWT token in Authorization header
- User must be in same organization as election
- Returns 403 Forbidden if accessing different org

**Rate Limiting**
- No rate limit (read-only operation)
- Caching recommended: Cache for 5 minutes

**Browser Support**
- Works with all modern browsers
- CORS enabled for documented origins
```

